video.title: Arrow
video.synopsis: Based on DC Comics' Green Arrow, an affluent playboy becomes a vengeful superhero, saving the city from villains armed with just a bow and arrows.

episodes.synopsis: Presumed dead for five years before being discovered on a remote Pacific island, billionaire playboy Oliver Queen returns home a changed man.
episodes.title: Pilot

episodes.synopsis: Oliver sets his sights on taking down a criminal with ties to the Chinese triad: Martin Somers, who's being prosecuted by Laurel.
episodes.title: Honor Thy Father

episodes.synopsis: When a gunman kills one of Oliver's targets, he enlists Det. Lance's help. Meanwhile, Laurel and Tommy find themselves caught in an awkward situation.
episodes.title: Lone Gunmen

episodes.synopsis: While looking into a murder case, Oliver realizes that one of the targets on his list has framed an innocent man for the crime.
episodes.title: An Innocent Man

episodes.synopsis: When Oliver is arrested for murder, he insists that Laurel represent him in court. She takes the case, putting her at odds with her father.
episodes.title: Damaged

episodes.synopsis: A band of bank robbers dubbed the Royal Flush Gang seriously wounds an off-duty police officer during a heist, forcing Oliver to rethink his mission.
episodes.title: Legacies

episodes.synopsis: The Huntress arrives in Starling City and puts Oliver under her spell. Meanwhile, adverse events blindside Tommy, who turns to Laurel for support.
episodes.title: Muse of Fire

episodes.synopsis: Oliver trains Helena to be his ally. Later, her pursuit of vengeance leads Helena to kill the leader of the triad.
episodes.title: Vendetta

episodes.synopsis: Determined to make up for lost time and restore a sense of normality to the Queen household, Oliver throws a family Christmas party.
episodes.title: Year's End

episodes.synopsis: After the Dark Archer defeats Oliver, he loses confidence and takes a break from being Arrow -- until Laurel needs help probing a firefighter's death.
episodes.title: Burned

episodes.synopsis: Oliver suspects that Diggle's mentor is responsible for some armored truck robberies. Meanwhile, Thea believes Moira and Malcolm are having an affair.
episodes.title: Trust but Verify

episodes.synopsis: Thea finds herself in legal trouble after getting caught with a drug called Vertigo. Meanwhile, Felicity gives Oliver disturbing news about Moira.
episodes.title: Vertigo

episodes.synopsis: A nasty crook released from prison plans to reclaim his place as leader of Starling City's underworld but first must take down his biggest foe: Arrow.
episodes.title: Betrayal

episodes.synopsis: When Oliver is shot, he turns to Felicity for help. While hovering between life and death, he flashes back to a daring escape attempt on the island.
episodes.title: The Odyssey

episodes.synopsis: Oliver asks Det. McKenna Hall on a date. Meanwhile, a jewel thief named Dodger hits Starling City and targets someone close to Oliver.
episodes.title: Dodger

episodes.synopsis: Oliver and Diggle learn that Deadshot is still alive and that Malcolm is the next target. Meanwhile, Oliver urges Tommy to reconcile with his father.
episodes.title: Dead to Rights

episodes.synopsis: The Huntress returns to town and threatens to destroy everything and everyone Oliver cares about. Later, Steve Aoki headlines the nightclub opening.
episodes.title: The Huntress Returns

episodes.synopsis: An angry resident of the Glades embarks on a kidnapping and killing spree to punish those he believes have wronged the residents of his neighborhood.
episodes.title: Salvation

episodes.synopsis: When a young woman meets a violent death after partying at Verdant, Det. Lance uncovers incriminating evidence against Tommy.
episodes.title: Unfinished Business

episodes.synopsis: When Deadshot returns to Starling City after taking down a U.S. ambassador and six others abroad, a sting operation is launched to capture him alive.
episodes.title: Home Invasion

episodes.synopsis: As Oliver focuses on crossing another name off the list, Felicity finds a transaction on a shady accountant's laptop that may help him locate Walter.
episodes.title: The Undertaking

episodes.synopsis: With the Undertaking just days away, Malcolm dons his black hood to conclude business with seismologist Brion Markov and his team.
episodes.title: Darkness on the Edge of Town

episodes.synopsis: In the season finale, Oliver and Diggle try to stop the Dark Archer from unleashing his vengeance on the Glades. Meanwhile, Thea races to find Roy.
episodes.title: Sacrifice

episodes.synopsis: With Starling City and Queen Consolidated deteriorating fast, Diggle and Felicity travel to Lian Yu Island to convince Oliver to return as the Arrow.
episodes.title: City of Heroes

episodes.synopsis: Oliver learns that medicine is being hijacked on the way to Glades Memorial Hospital, leading to a showdown with Bronze Tiger and China White.
episodes.title: Identity

episodes.synopsis: Felicity offers herself as bait so Arrow, Diggle and Lance can catch a criminal who broke out of prison and is torturing and murdering women.
episodes.title: Broken Dolls

episodes.synopsis: Oliver learns that a man known as "The Mayor" is bringing illegal guns into the Glades, so he sponsors a cash for guns event to clean up the city.
episodes.title: Crucible

episodes.synopsis: Oliver tries to get the Canary to reveal her background. Meanwhile, the Assistant District Attorney offers Moira a life-or-death deal.
episodes.title: League of Assassins

episodes.synopsis: Diggle learns that Lyla is missing after following a lead in Moscow. Moira's lawyer tells Thea that dating Roy is hurting her mother's case.
episodes.title: Keep Your Enemies Closer

episodes.synopsis: A mysterious illness sweeps the city, infecting hundreds of people -- including Diggle. Moira goes on trial for her participation in the Undertaking.
episodes.title: State v. Queen

episodes.synopsis: A seemingly impossible robbery at Queen Consolidated's Applied Sciences Division brings Central City police scientist Barry Allen to town.
episodes.title: The Scientist

episodes.synopsis: Oliver is visited by ghosts from the past. Meanwhile, Barry continues to help Felicity, and their connection grows stronger.
episodes.title: Three Ghosts

episodes.synopsis: Oliver must tackle a new threat when bombs start to go off in Starling City, and Thea witnesses Roy's super-strength in action.
episodes.title: Blast Radius

episodes.synopsis: Arrow teams up with Laurel to find the Man in the Mask, and when Sin tests Roy's superstrength, the results are nearly fatal.
episodes.title: Blind Spot

episodes.synopsis: Arrow offers to teach Roy to control his superstrength, but Roy proves to be a rebellious student. Meanwhile, the Bronze Tiger becomes a threat again.
episodes.title: Tremors

episodes.synopsis: Sara is forced to make an important decision when her past with the League of Assassins comes back to haunt her -- and her family.
episodes.title: Heir to the Demon

episodes.synopsis: The team goes after the Clock King, who has tech that can open any bank vault in Starling City, while Sara ruffles Queen's feathers.
episodes.title: Time of Death

episodes.synopsis: Back on the island where Oliver spent years shipwrecked, his plan with Slade and Sara to take over a freighter from Ivo takes a deadly turn.
episodes.title: The Promise

episodes.synopsis: With Slade back and vowing revenge on Oliver's loved ones, Oliver prepares for battle; Diggle is recruited by A.R.G.U.S. to stop a warlord.
episodes.title: Suicide Squad

episodes.synopsis: When Frank Bertinelli is arrested and Laurel is picked to try the case, Bertinelli's daughter, the Huntress, returns with her own take on justice.
episodes.title: Birds of Prey

episodes.synopsis: Slade makes his move against Oliver, with enormous repercussions. Meanwhile, Isabel attempts to take Queen Consolidated away from Oliver.
episodes.title: Deathstroke

episodes.synopsis: After an epic battle with Slade, one member of Team Arrow is sent to the hospital, and Oliver is forced to make a tough decision involving Thea.
episodes.title: The Man Under the Hood

episodes.synopsis: When the team realizes that the Mirakuru has taken over Roy completely, rendering him deadly and out of control, they're forced to take action.
episodes.title: Seeing Red

episodes.synopsis: To stop Slade, Oliver may have to make the ultimate sacrifice, but Diggle and Felicity go to extreme measures to stop him.
episodes.title: City of Blood

episodes.synopsis: Oliver and his team rally to stop Slade's soldiers as they attack Starling City. Meanwhile, Malcolm Merlyn returns.
episodes.title: Streets of Fire

episodes.synopsis: Oliver's no-kill rule is put to the ultimate test when Slade kidnaps someone close to Oliver's heart. Meanwhile, Diggle takes on Amanda Waller.
episodes.title: Unthinkable

episodes.synopsis: In the wake of Slade's downfall, the peaceful city celebrates, but Werner Zytle has a deadly plot up his sleeve, and a homicidal archer targets Sara.
episodes.title: The Calm

episodes.synopsis: Oliver pursues a murderous archer; Laurel tries to take justice for Sara's death into her own hands; Thea makes progress in her training with Merlyn.
episodes.title: Sara

episodes.synopsis: Oliver trails Thea to an island, hoping to bring her back to Starling City; Oliver helps Diggle find a missing ARGUS agent; Laurel tries to toughen up.
episodes.title: Corto Maltese

episodes.synopsis: When Oliver sends Roy out to tail Nyssa and learn more about Sara's killer, Thea gets kidnapped, and Oliver makes a dangerous enemy.
episodes.title: The Magician

episodes.synopsis: Felicity investigates a cyberattack on Starling City and discovers that she herself created the virus; Roy's nightmares tell him that he killed Sara.
episodes.title: The Secret Origin of Felicity Smoak

episodes.synopsis: When bodies appear at the gym, Oliver helps prove Ted Grant's innocence and catch the killer; Roy faces the aftermath of the Mirakuru virus.
episodes.title: Guilty

episodes.synopsis: Oliver investigates a menace named Cupid, who is romantically obsessed with him; Oliver feels pangs of jealousy over Ray's rapport with Felicity.
episodes.title: Draw Back Your Bow

episodes.synopsis: A boomerang-wielding murderer defies Oliver's team and ARGUS; Digger lays a trap for Lyla with the intent to kill her and whomever stands in his way.
episodes.title: The Brave and the Bold

episodes.synopsis: The League of Assassins issues a terrifying threat; the DNA results of Sara's murder investigation shock Felicity; Oliver faces a formidable foe.
episodes.title: The Climb

episodes.synopsis: With the Arrow gone, Diggle and Roy strive to protect Starling City as a new crime lord plots a power grab; Merlyn finds evidence of Oliver's demise.
episodes.title: Left Behind

episodes.synopsis: Maseo and Tatsu must go to extremes to protect the healing Oliver; Brick kidnaps a city official and tries to banish the police force from the Glades.
episodes.title: Midnight City

episodes.synopsis: Oliver finds a mentor to help him bring down Ra's; Capt. Lance advises Roy and Laurel on fighting Brick's men; Merlyn discovers who killed his wife.
episodes.title: Uprising

episodes.synopsis: When Laurel tries to capture Zytle after his prison break, he doses her with his poison, Vertigo; DJ Chase tries to murder League trainee Thea.
episodes.title: Canaries

episodes.synopsis: As Oliver starts training Thea on the island of Lian Yu, Slade captures and imprisons them, and Thea is forced to face a painful truth.
episodes.title: The Return

episodes.synopsis: Oliver sets out to rescue Merlyn to keep Thea from disconnecting with her humanity once she realizes that she has sealed her father's dire fate.
episodes.title: Nanda Parbat

episodes.synopsis: With a plot in mind, Ra's pushes Oliver to take over the League, revealing the secret of his longevity; Capt. Lance withdraws his support of Arrow.
episodes.title: The Offer

episodes.synopsis: A honeymoon for Diggle and Lyla is cut short when they are recruited for a dangerous rescue mission; an Arrow imposter murders the mayor.
episodes.title: Suicidal Tendencies

episodes.synopsis: Arrow's team is hunted down for the mayor's murder; a wound threatens Ray's life; Ra's kidnaps Captain Lance and exposes Arrow's identity.
episodes.title: Public Enemy

episodes.synopsis: When Roy is arrested, Oliver's crew plots to spring him from prison and protect Arrow's identity; Ray needs Oliver's help to bring down Jake Simmons.
episodes.title: Broken Arrow

episodes.synopsis: When Oliver tries to bring Thea back from the brink of death, he is forced to renounce his old life and step into a new role with the League.
episodes.title: The Fallen

episodes.synopsis: Oliver takes on a new identity and a daunting test of allegiance; Ra's recalls dueling his best friend to become the leader of the League.
episodes.title: Al Sah-him

episodes.synopsis: Diggle and Laurel patrol Starling City; Oliver learns who provided Ra's with the Omega virus and confesses the truth about his place in the League.
episodes.title: This Is Your Sword

episodes.synopsis: Oliver and his team race to stop Ra's from releasing the virus and destroying Starling City, but as the dust settles, Oliver makes a fateful choice.
episodes.title: My Name is Oliver Queen

episodes.synopsis: When Damien Darhk attacks newly renamed Star City with a gang of assassins, Oliver rebuffs an old ally and returns as the Green Arrow to fight back.
episodes.title: Green Arrow

episodes.synopsis: Green Arrow and Speedy track an assassin who targets a family friend. Meanwhile, Thea's bloodlust escalates, and Oliver decides to run for mayor.
episodes.title: The Candidate

episodes.synopsis: While Thea and Laurel try to revive Sara with the Lazarus Pit, Oliver and Diggle must make peace and team up in order to confront a new assassin.
episodes.title: Restoration

episodes.synopsis: While Oliver sets a trap to catch a group of crooked cops, Laurel takes Quentin to see Sara, who is feral and chained up in Laurel's basement.
episodes.title: Beyond Redemption

episodes.synopsis: When Sara turns savage, Oliver calls in John Constantine to restore her soul to her body. Meanwhile, Diggle learns the truth about his brother.
episodes.title: Haunted

episodes.synopsis: Learning that the explosion miniaturized Ray, the team launches a mission to rescue him from Damien Darhk and return him to normal size.
episodes.title: Lost Souls

episodes.synopsis: Thea discovers a potential but risky cure for her bloodlust, and the team asks Ray for help when they learn that Andy is alive but working for Darhk.
episodes.title: Brotherhood

episodes.synopsis: Oliver and Barry use ingenuity and a little time travel to protect Carter Hall and Kendra Saunders from immortal assassin Vandal Savage.
episodes.title: Legends of Yesterday

episodes.synopsis: After Oliver exposes him as the force behind H.I.V.E., Darhk kidnaps Diggle, Thea and Felicity, prompting Oliver to take a desperate gamble.
episodes.title: Dark Waters

episodes.synopsis: Desperate to get revenge for Felicity's near-fatal wounding, Oliver uses freelance anarchist Lonnie Machin to go on the hunt for Damien Darhk.
episodes.title: Blood Debts

episodes.synopsis: While Felicity adapts to her new role in Team Arrow, Diggle and Andy help Oliver track sinister Shadowspire operatives trying to infiltrate A.R.G.U.S.
episodes.title: A.W.O.L.

episodes.synopsis: Oliver and Thea get a surprise when they chase a burglar being controlled by a villain named the Calculator, who has a dire plan for Star City.
episodes.title: Unchained

episodes.synopsis: Hoping to obtain a cure for Thea's bloodlust, Oliver pits Nyssa and Malcolm against each other in a battle for control of the League of Assassins.
episodes.title: Sins of the Father

episodes.synopsis: Darhk dispatches mercenaries to blow up key targets in Star City, including the venue where mayoral candidate Oliver plans to debate his opponent.
episodes.title: Code of Silence

episodes.synopsis: Vixen uses her mystical powers to help Team Arrow trigger a showdown with Darhk. Meanwhile, the truth drives a wedge between Oliver and Felicity.
episodes.title: Taken

episodes.synopsis: When Cupid returns and begins attacking newlyweds, recently estranged Oliver and Felicity lay a trap for her by going through with their wedding.
episodes.title: Broken Hearts

episodes.synopsis: Desperate to get her hands on Felicity's microchip implant, Brie Larvan escapes prison and attacks Palmer Tech, using robotic bees to fend off Oliver.
episodes.title: Beacon of Hope

episodes.synopsis: Oliver and Diggle discover that Malcolm has a plan to spring Darhk from prison. Meanwhile, Laurel gets a tempting offer.
episodes.title: Eleven-Fifty-Nine

episodes.synopsis: When the Black Canary strikes again, Oliver and Quentin spar over Laurel's fate. Meanwhile, a plot targets Mayor Adams, and Oliver vows to kill Darhk.
episodes.title: Canary Cry

episodes.synopsis: Felicity and Oliver seek out a shaman who reveals the source of Darhk's magical powers, and the team uncovers his sinister master plan.
episodes.title: Genesis

episodes.synopsis: As Darhk launches his cataclysmic plot, Oliver and the team turn to Felicity's father to thwart it. But H.I.V.E. also has him in their sights.
episodes.title: Monument Point

episodes.synopsis: Darhk renews his efforts to carry out his doomsday plan, and Oliver and Diggle infiltrate a secret H.I.V.E. facility in search of Thea.
episodes.title: Lost in the Flood

episodes.synopsis: While the team scrambles desperately to avert a global cataclysm, Oliver draws on a surprising power to confront Darhk once and for all.
episodes.title: Schism

episodes.synopsis: While Felicity pushes to bring in new recruits and Oliver grapples with letting go of the past, brutal crook Tobias Church begins his ascent to power.
episodes.title: Legacy

episodes.synopsis: Green Arrow tries to train new recruits but must do some soul-searching first. Meanwhile, Church makes a move to ensure his domination of Star City.
episodes.title: Recruits

episodes.synopsis: Insolent Wild Dog deserts the new team to take on a drug kingpin by himself, forcing Green Arrow into a dangerous showdown.
episodes.title: A Matter of Trust

episodes.synopsis: With Oliver out on a mission to free Diggle, Church mounts an attack against Star City. Can the new team meet the threat without their leader?
episodes.title: Penance

episodes.synopsis: While he faces an assassination threat as mayor, Oliver turns to old ally Human Target to help rescue Wild Dog from Church's clutches.
episodes.title: Human Target

episodes.synopsis: Believing that Prometheus's lethal rampage is meant to send him a message, Green Arrow tries to unravel the mystery while keeping his team from harm.
episodes.title: So It Begins

episodes.synopsis: Green Arrow and the team wrangle over a deadly new vigilante prowling Star City's streets, and Thea stands up for Quentin after he reveals a secret.
episodes.title: Vigilante

episodes.synopsis: When aliens invade, team Green Arrow joins forces with Flash, Supergirl and the time-traveling Legends of Tomorrow to face the intergalactic threat.
episodes.title: Invasion

episodes.synopsis: After a vicious attack reveals that Prometheus knows all their secrets, the team faces a shocking betrayal from one of their own.
episodes.title: What We Leave Behind

episodes.synopsis: A surprise doppelganger sets Green Arrow and Felicity at odds, and DA Chase tangles with military brass to save Diggle from a virtual death sentence.
episodes.title: Who Are You?

episodes.synopsis: Green Arrow's search for a new Black Canary turns up a promising but loose-cannon candidate. Felicity tries to hack into the NSA to liberate Diggle.
episodes.title: Second Chances

episodes.synopsis: A grave new threat takes the team to Russia, where Oliver runs afoul of an old Bratva comrade. In Star City, Rene faces a test of leadership.
episodes.title: Bratva

episodes.synopsis: A brutal attack on city hall forces Oliver to seek justice as Mayor Queen, not Green Arrow. Rene relives his journey from family man to masked hero.
episodes.title: Spectre of the Gun

episodes.synopsis: After a jailbreak, Green Arrow's hunt to apprehend vengeful villains Liza Warner, Cupid and China White faces shocking interference from the ACU.
episodes.title: The Sin-Eater

episodes.synopsis: After being targeted by Vigilante, Oliver fights impeachment proceedings at city hall while Diggle and the team angle to take out Vigilante for good.
episodes.title: Fighting Fire with Fire

episodes.synopsis: Green Arrow closes in on the true identity of Prometheus, who takes a hostage close to Oliver's heart. Felicity faces an ultimatum from Helix.
episodes.title: Checkmate

episodes.synopsis: Now unmasked, Prometheus sinks his claws into Oliver to exact revenge and elicit a confession about Green Arrow's dark and violent past.
episodes.title: Kapiushon

episodes.synopsis: Dissension rends Team Green Arrow when Oliver calls on his old -- and volatile -- Bratva allies to eliminate Prometheus once and for all.
episodes.title: Disbanded

episodes.synopsis: With all of Star City on the hunt for Adrian Chase, Felicity defies Oliver and turns to Helix for help -- but their assistance comes at a steep price.
episodes.title: Dangerous Liaisons

episodes.synopsis: A mysterious explosion disables Felicity and traps Oliver and her alone in the bunker. Diggle and Lyla face issues in their marriage.
episodes.title: Underneath

episodes.synopsis: The hunt for Adrian Chase leads Team Arrow to a confrontation with Sampson. A macabre delivery at city hall sends Oliver a disturbing message.
episodes.title: Honor Thy Fathers

episodes.synopsis: A friendly surprise catches Oliver off guard, and the team scrambles when they discover that Adrian Chase has begun hunting them down, one by one.
episodes.title: Missing

episodes.synopsis: Desperate to save his team and family, Oliver returns to the island of Lian Yu and recruits an old foe for a climactic showdown with Adrian Chase.
episodes.title: Lian Yu

episodes.synopsis: While Quentin struggles to make peace with his actions back on Lian Yu, Black Siren begins a bombing campaign against the SCPD and Team Green Arrow.
episodes.title: The Fallout

episodes.synopsis: A dogged FBI agent targets Oliver in the wake of an incriminating leaked photo. Anatoly makes a daring strike. Diggle faces a difficult truth.
episodes.title: Tribute

episodes.synopsis: Diggle steps into his new role but faces a crisis of leadership when the team races to thwart a poison gas attack by Onyx and her crew.
episodes.title: Next of Kin

episodes.synopsis: As a series of perplexing murders unfolds across Star City, Felicity races to thwart an impending cataclysmic attack by Cayden James.
episodes.title: Reversal

episodes.synopsis: With Oliver's help, Slade tracks his missing son but makes a terrible discovery. A distressing revelation spurs Dinah to hunt down a rogue sniper.
episodes.title: Deathstroke Returns

episodes.synopsis: Slade's quest to reunite with his son takes an ominous turn. Diggle's secret collides with the team's mission to take down a slippery drug dealer.
episodes.title: Promises Kept

episodes.synopsis: Oliver's holiday plans are cut short when Watson arrests him, prompting Cayden James and Black Siren to unleash an attack at a Star City rock concert.
episodes.title: Thanksgiving

episodes.synopsis: Green Arrow joins Supergirl, the Flash and the Legends of Tomorrow to combat the Nazi invasion from Earth-X -- and an evil doppelgänger of himself.
episodes.title: Crisis on Earth-X, Part 2

episodes.synopsis: The team celebrates a long-expected wedding but discovers a traitor in their midst. Cayden James forces Oliver into a mission-impossible heist.
episodes.title: Irreconcilable Differences

episodes.synopsis: A wedge driven between them, the team discovers that their bunker is compromised. A mob boss turns to Green Arrow for help against a common enemy.
episodes.title: Divided

episodes.synopsis: Oliver scrambles to secure Star City after Cayden James unleashes a deadly, high-tech siege. Dinah and the new team clash over a shifty new ally.
episodes.title: We Fall

episodes.synopsis: While Cayden James hunts for a mole on his team, Felicity initiates a risky plan to neutralize the thermobaric bomb menacing Star City.
episodes.title: All for Nothing

episodes.synopsis: His old team in disarray, Oliver faces an ultimatum from Cayden James. Meanwhile, Dinah's thirst for vengeance drives her to go rogue.
episodes.title: The Devil's Greatest Trick

episodes.synopsis: While Star City faces financial ruin, former allies come to a violent crossroads over the fate of Black Siren. Meanwhile, Quentin harbors a secret.
episodes.title: Collision Course

episodes.synopsis: Learning that Roy Harper has been taken captive in Star City, Thea takes up her Speedy suit and rejoins Team Green Arrow for a daring rescue mission.
episodes.title: Doppelgänger

episodes.synopsis: A group of assassins on their trail, Nyssa, Thea and Team Green Arrow work to hack a cryptic map. Dinah and Curtis hunt for corrupt cops.
episodes.title: The Thanatos Guild

episodes.synopsis: Diaz moves to consolidate his control of Star City. Diggle confronts Oliver over his leadership of the team -- and comes to a pivotal crossroads.
episodes.title: Brothers in Arms

episodes.synopsis: Pressures mounting on all sides, Oliver suffers troubling hallucinations that expose his deepest insecurities and send him down a dangerous path.
episodes.title: Fundamentals

episodes.synopsis: As Diaz takes a meeting with far-reaching consequences for Star City, Felicity and Curtis work on taking Helix Dynamics to the next level.
episodes.title: The Dragon

episodes.synopsis: Oliver rolls the dice to turn Anatoly against Diaz. Rene returns to the fight as Dinah's team and Diggle join forces to take on the Quadrant.
episodes.title: Shifting Allegiances

episodes.synopsis: Oliver faces life in prison as his case plays out in court, but the trial takes an unexpected turn when an old friend makes a surprise appearance.
episodes.title: Docket No. 11-19-41-73

episodes.synopsis: Facing a coordinated all-out assault, the members of Team Green Arrow reunite to steal data that could break Diaz's iron grip on Star City.
episodes.title: The Ties That Bind

episodes.synopsis: With Star City hanging in the balance, a new ally joins the fight alongside Team Green Arrow as Oliver drives Diaz to an explosive showdown.
episodes.title: Life Sentence

episodes.synopsis: While Oliver fights to keep his cool in harsh new surroundings, Felicity comes under fire and a new vigilante posing as Green Arrow hits the streets.
episodes.title: Inmate 4587

episodes.synopsis: Team Green Arrow reassembles to track down the Longbow Hunters after a theft at A.R.G.U.S. Oliver makes a dicey bargain in Slabside.
episodes.title: Longbow Hunters

episodes.synopsis: Oliver faces a formidable challenge behind bars, Felicity makes her priorities crystal clear, and Curtis creates a technical masterpiece.
episodes.title: Crossing Lines

episodes.synopsis: Under interrogation, Oliver reconsiders his legacy. While an arsonist burns the Glades, Dinah and Rene lock horns over the new Green Arrow.
episodes.title: Level Two

episodes.synopsis: Locked in the brutal depths of Slabside, Oliver hatches an escape plan with an old foe. Curtis faces an identity crisis while going undercover.
episodes.title: The Demon

episodes.synopsis: Over Oliver's objections, Laurel takes up his case. Felicity pushes an undercover op to the edge. Oliver takes a stand for a friend in Slabside.
episodes.title: Due	Process

episodes.synopsis: Putting his freedom in jeopardy, Oliver forces a showdown after Diaz infiltrates Slabside with a ruthless plan for revenge.
episodes.title: The	Slabside	Redemption

episodes.synopsis: After his release from Slabside, Oliver helps Rene and Dinah as they try to learn the identity of the new Green Arrow, who is suspected of murder.
episodes.title: Unmasked

episodes.synopsis: Oliver, Kara and Barry get some unexpected help in their search for answers in Gotham City. Meanwhile, Felicity makes an interdimensional breakthrough.
episodes.title: Elseworlds: Hour Two

episodes.synopsis: Rene fights to help the new Green Arrow's mission, and Oliver, now working with the SCPD, finds an unexpected link to the mysterious vigilante.
episodes.title: My Name is Emiko Queen

episodes.synopsis: His father's legacy haunts Oliver's attempt to regain Star City's trust. John pressures Curtis into helping with the revived Ghost Initiative.
episodes.title: Past Sins

episodes.synopsis: While a documentary film crew dogs his steps, Oliver goes on the hunt for a mysterious masked figure who has begun targeting Star City's vigilantes.
episodes.title: Emerald Archer

episodes.synopsis: Dinah and her freshly deputized crew slip into a horror-movie scenario while chasing a creepy serial killer. William and Oliver clash over their future.
episodes.title: Star City Slayer

episodes.synopsis: Felicity aims to take out Diaz when Diggle sends the Ghost Initiative after Dante. Oliver steps in as Emiko searches for her mother's killer.
episodes.title: Brothers & Sisters

episodes.synopsis: Chafing under new rules, the members of Team Arrow -- now SCPD recruits -- go after a dealer putting chemical weapons on the streets of Star City.
episodes.title: Training Day

episodes.synopsis: Decades in the future, William and Mia take their perilous quest to the Glades, where they make some disturbing -- and dangerous -- discoveries.
episodes.title: Star City 2040

episodes.synopsis: While Team Arrow picks up Dante's trail at last, Laurel clashes with Dinah and Oliver discovers an alarming secret about Emiko's past.
episodes.title: Inheritance

episodes.synopsis: With her criminal history now out in the open, Laurel joins forces with an old acquaintance. Meanwhile, Dinah and Felicity do battle.
episodes.title: Lost Canary

episodes.synopsis: After Archer falls into the hands of the Ninth Circle, Diggle calls in some big guns for help -- and must face his family's conflicted past.
episodes.title: Spartan

episodes.synopsis: Trying to unravel a mystery, the SCPD interrogates Team Arrow after their off-the-books mission to thwart a bio-terrorism attack turns deadly.
episodes.title: Confessions

episodes.synopsis: While Team Arrow races to rescue him from the rubble of a collapsed building, Oliver faces a moment of truth. Emiko has another surprise in store.
episodes.title: Living Proof

episodes.synopsis: Team Arrow races to thwart Emiko's bioterror attack while Oliver tries to liberate her from their family's cycle of violence. Oliver's debt comes due.
episodes.title: You Have Saved This City

episodes.synopsis: The Dark Archer casts a shadow over a bittersweet family reunion in a parallel universe as Oliver desperately tries to track the dwarf star particles.
episodes.title: Starling City

episodes.synopsis: With an altered Earth-2 in his rearview and the fate of the multiverse at stake, Oliver gets a new task and reunites with a kick-ass old comrade.
episodes.title: Welcome to Hong Kong

episodes.synopsis: It seems like old times, but much has changed: Thea bonds with Oliver, while John and Lyla team up. Back in the future, Mia takes the lead -- at a cost.
episodes.title: Leap of Faith

episodes.synopsis: It's not the family reunion that a proud papa would ask for, but Oliver tries to get up to speed. Can he build trust to replace the rage and pain?
episodes.title: Present Tense

episodes.synopsis: Oliver takes his training to the next level and journeys with Mia and Will to a challenging place from his past. Laurel discovers an unexpected ally.
episodes.title: Prochnost

episodes.synopsis: It feels like a rerun -- or an insidious time loop -- when Oliver wakes to find Quentin alive. Now he must find a way to halt the hellish reboot.
episodes.title: Reset

episodes.synopsis: Back on Lian Yu, Oliver and the team are charged with building a megaweapon for a space god, all while fighting the nightmarish isle’s army of ghosts.
episodes.title: Purgatory

episodes.synopsis: After revisiting his epic clashes, Oliver joins the fight to save everyone. The Paragons must travel to the dawn of time and face the Anti-Monitor.
episodes.title: Crisis on Infinite Earths: Hour Four

episodes.synopsis: When a socialite goes missing, Laurel and Dinah must convince a reluctant Mia to take up her father's mantle to keep chaos from engulfing Star City.
episodes.title: Green Arrow & The Canaries

episodes.synopsis: In the aftermath of the Crisis, in an altered world, the survivors regroup, remember and look to the future. But is the mission ever really over?
episodes.title: Fadeout
